$interpreted: Crushfang: ...If the Kingdom of the Sun continues to trespass and steal the sacred gem rocks of Totemtaff,
Crushfang: The Bears will not give in.
Angelia: Rune devices need gem rocks to function. Those Sun folks were left with no choice. They did what they had to in order to survive.
Angelia: If the Bears and my Kingdom mined together, we could put an end to this feud. Will Chieftain Crushfang reconsider once more?
Crushfang: Impossible.
Angelia: Th-Th-Then under the Bears' supervision, we keep mining to an acceptable minimum?
Crushfang: Bears are not babysitters. Besides, we don't have the extra bearpower.

Angelia: How about the Sunshine Infantry?
Colonel Dylan is a trustworthy man...
Crushfang: And the princess thinks I will let more castle forces enter Totemtaff?
Angelia: This... there must be a way, let me think...

Angelia: Well, what if this was handled like a contract?
Your tribe names a price...
Crushfang: Your Highness. With all due respect, even if a verdict is reached here, will the Kingdom of the Sun honor it?
Angelia: Well, all policies do have to be approved by my uncle, His Majesty King Theodore.
Angelia: However, in three months I'll be of age, and the Kingdom's policies will...

Crushfang: If that is so, perhaps wait until Highness reigns.
It won't be too late to discuss.
Angelia: ………
Dagger: HEY. Chieftain Crushfang, there's no need to speak like that?
Angelia: Sir Dagger, it's alright, really. It's my fault for being unprepared and disturbing Chieftain Crushfang.
Angelia: Chieftain Crushfang. Until we meet again, I will definitely work on preparing a proposal worthy of the Bears.
Crushfang: You... you're just as I thought.
Angelia: And what does Chieftain Crushfang mean by that?
Crushfang: Your ancestors enforced harsh policies, greatly affecting the Bears' way of life. But, your father, King William, proposed a meeting,
Crushfang: hoping to make peace and amend for past sins.
Angelia: My father?
Crushfang: The Chieftain before me kindly refused the offer. Time proved to us that your father was a benevolent leader, indeed, a rare gem.
Crushfang: This is the reason I decided to meet you this time.
Angelia: I see. If it were father, he would have proposed something much better...
Crushfang: Patience. Never forget that your motive is to serve the people. Stay humble and you will eventually become who you were meant to be.
Crushfang: One day, you will become a leader worthy of everyone's respect, just like your father.
Angelia: I understand. Thank you, Chieftain Crushfang.
Crushfang: Dagger, escort Princess Angelia on her way out.
Dagger: Understood. Princess, this way, please!
Old Priest: The way he speaks to her.
Crushfang: Oh, so you've noticed that too?
